h=100 height=150></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_eyes.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Dark Truths in Class Balance</span><hr size=1> Some dark truths I see between Paladins Shadowknights and Warriors, from observations playing with close online friends.<br>
<br>
 Paladins tank boss mobs and have wizards chain nuke, insane no risk encounters. <br>
<br>
A level 65 Paladin  is a level 65 melee and a level 50<br>
cleric. They have fantastic group heals incredibly high aggro<br>
from cease and desist, great group buffs. Divine aura allows them to make pulls no one else can. <br>
LOH is a great emergency ability.<br>
 survivability through mitigation 95 percent of that of  a warrior. <br>
Self buffs 1730 hitpoints 68 ac 3 mana regen.<br>
group buffs 1388 hitpoints 38ac<br>
<br>
preferred as:<br>
<br>
Non damage add tanker<br>
Group tanker<br>
<br>
Can tank most boss mobs with high aggro<br>
<br>
A level 65 Shadowknight is a level 65 melee but isn't close<br>
to the power of a level 50 necromancer. Pretty terrible<br>
or non existant group buffs. Good aggro through darkness.<br>
Feign death next to useless on any pull that is a caster.<br>
Harmtouch is an ok emergency ability in the right circumstances, resistable. Survivability through mitigation<br>
95 percent that of a warrior, <br>
Self buffs 279 hitpoints ac 18 10 damage shield attack 200<br>
<br>
Non damage add tanker<br>
Group tanker<br>
<br>
Can tank most boss mobs with high aggro<br>
<br>
A level 65 Warrior is a level 65 melee and a level 20 melee.<br>
Defensive emergency ability 40 percent increased mitigation, 40 percent decrease in DPS, many boss mobs designed around this &quot;emergency ability&quot;.<br>
100 percent survivability through mitgation.<br>
No self buffs, zero utility<br>
<br>
Cannot hold aggro well enough to non damage add tank<br>
Not preferred in groups<br>
Can tank all boss mobs with low aggro.<br>
<br>
Current all/all itemization rewards Knights through the addition of mana wis/int but does nothing for warriors.<br>
<br>
Currently Warriors are in PRE-Kunark, where they first started<br>
as Paladins or Shadowknights without spells.<br>
<br>
