<br>
Starting with the junk, NO ONE invites a paladin over a warrior for the buffs, hey theres a warrior with 1k more hps but he doesnt have that uber pally buff?  Or wait we need the paladin cuz he can root!  sure...<br>
<br>
Warriors generally have more hps, can do more damage, have better procing weapons, and can defensive if you get a named.  No one disputes any of that.  In raids those things count, but in xp groups the disparity in hps is meaningless, both have so many now that if a knight was gonna die the warrior is one or two blows later, a useful thing every once in a while but certainly not a reason to pick a warrior.  The extra dps is nice, but no one picks the MT based on that, theres too much variation in weapons between even warriors of the same level to make it a decision.<br>
<br>
Knights get in xp groups because they get agro faster and better than warriors.  Warriors get used on boss mobs for raid encounters.  Ive seen the articles bout knights and beastlords being used on quarm, but I could tank rublecrush with a monk - those people are severely overpowered and are bored with the encounter which isnt at all what we are talking about - we are talking bout regular folk, not tanks with 10k hps.  I do agree that warriors need better agro.  rather than fixing the rate at which they succeed id push for the refresh on taunt being shorter for them.  <br>
<br>
Having worked with good warriors they can hold agro almost as well as a paladin.  I can take agro from them if I REALLY want it (chain stunning)  but a boc plus good secondary with agro augs on em packs a ton of agro which requires no mana and always is on. <br>
<br>
What cant happen is warriors become superior to paladins in every way, I feel that many over rate paladin healing and utility spells.  I hear things like give warriors 2500 hit points more and equal or greater agro as paladins, and the paladins are supposed to be ok because they get root and some healing.  Paladins aren't supposed to be a lesser class, they are supposed to be a DIFFERENT class.  Id be glad to give warriors equal agro and more hitpoints if my pacify actually worked on anything id be remotely interested in fighting. but that (my best utility spell) hasnt been useful in a long long time.<br>
 <p>Caaine ShadowSlayer<br>
Proud leader of Immortals of Justice<br>
